57 (8) The use or consumption of electricity by an
58 incorporated municipality, a board, or corporation organized
59 under the authority of any incorporated municipality in
60 furnishing or providing street lighting or traffic-control
61 systems; the use or consumption of telephone services by an
62 incorporated municipality in providing fire alarm systems; and
63 the use or consumption of domestic water by an incorporated
64 municipality in extinguishing fires, explosions, or
65 conflagrations.
66 (9) The furnishing of natural gas or electricity for
67 use or consumption as fuel or energy in and for the heating of
68 commercial greenhouses, pivot irrigation systems, and poultry
69 houses.
70 (10) The furnishing of utility services through the use
71 of a prepaid telephone calling card."
72 "§40-21-103
73 The storage, use, or other consumption of utility
74 services in the State of Alabama is hereby specifically
75 excluded from the tax herein levied:
76 (1) Whenever the State of Alabama is prohibited from
77 taxing such storage, use, or consumption under the
78 Constitution or laws of the United States of America or the
79 Constitution of the State of Alabama of 2022;
80 (2) Whenever any tax relating to the sale, use,
81 storage, or consumption of said utility services shall be
82 levied under the provisions of Article 2 of Chapter 23 of this
83 title, or under the provisions of Sections 40-23-1 through
84 40-23-36 or the Alabama Transaction Tax Act of 1992 if enacted
